The paper deals with deep convolutional networks (CNNs) and recurrent networks such as LSTMs in the context of automatic speech recognition, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SD), or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Given that the paper focuses on the comparison and combination of CNNs and LSTMs, it is most likely to belong to cs.CL or cs.CV, which are the sub-categories that deal with these types of models in the context of language and image processing, respectively. However, since the paper also discusses model compression and efficiency, it could also be relevant to cs.LG, cs.SD, or cs.AI, which deal with these topics in the context of machine learning and artificial intelligence.
